Building enetc4_uio module:
==============================

ENETC4 UIO driver enables DPDK functionality on i.MX95/943 platforms with PHY
initialization support. The driver handles kernel-side hardware setup, leaving
rest of configuration to DPDK.

Prerequisites
-------------
The specific kernel source directory against which the driver
compilation is required must be compiled.

Build
------
$ cd enetc4_uio
$ make KSRC=/path/to/custom/kernel/source

The .ko file will be generated, which can be loaded using:
$ insmod enetc4_uio.ko

Clean
------
To clean the build directory, the following command can be run:

$ cd enetc4_uio
$ make KSRC=/path/to/custom/kernel/source clean
